{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Allow students who self-funded 1st degree to access student loan for 2nd degree",
        "additional_details": "Student loans are funded by the Government, and so the taxpayer, so that students can pursue an education that will hopefully land them a job and in turn become taxpayers who pay off their loans to replenish the system.\r\n \r\nWe believe that the existing rules, where an applicant who has self-funded their first degree is not eligible for a student loan, is draconian since the applicant has not previously accessed a student loan.",
        "background": "To change the eligibility for student loans so that home students who have self-funded for their 1st Bachelor, Master or Doctorate degree can still be eligible to access a student loan for their 2nd degree at the same level as the 1st.",
